Package soot.jimple.infoflow.android.callbacks.filters

Interface ICallbackFilter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCallbackFilter, AlienFragmentFilter, AlienHostComponentFilter, ApplicationCallbackFilter, UnreachableConstructorFilter
    public interface ICallbackFilter
    Common interface for all callback filters. A callback filter takes the discovered associations between host components and callbacks and filters out those that are not of interest to the analysis.
    Author:
    Steven Arzt

    • Method Detail

      • accepts

        boolean accepts​(soot.SootClass component,
                soot.SootClass callbackHandler)
        Checks whether the given callback handler is usable in the given Android component
        Parameters:
        component - The component at whose runtime the callback is to be invoked
        callbackHandler - The class containing the callback implementation
        Returns:
        True if the filter accepts the callback to be registered, otherwise false

      • setReachableMethods

        void setReachableMethods​(ComponentReachableMethods rm)
        Sets the analysis that can provide the methods that are reachable inside the app. A callback analysis is free to pass a new analysis into the filter when changing its scope, e.g., when processing a new component.
        Parameters:
        rm - The reachable methods analysis
